From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 07:51:42 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: return error for wrong region commit attempts

It is DAMON API caller's responsibility to prevent passing invalid
monitoring target regions.  All callers are doing that well, but future
callers might not.  All callers will have to pass the parameters
validation in DAMON core layer.  Add a validation of regions in the core
validation to prevent possible future violations and deduplicate same
validations in callers.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index 2f161736722c2..b8b102b263259 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -1526,6 +1526,8 @@ static int damon_commit_target_regions(struct damon_target *dst,
 	int i = 0, err;
 
 	damon_for_each_region(src_region, src) {
+		if (src_region->ar.start >= src_region->ar.end)
+			return -EINVAL;
 		if (!prev || prev->ar.end != src_region->ar.start)
 			i++;
 		prev = src_region;
-- 
2.47.3

